## Conclusion

Protecting the environment requires a multifaceted approach combining individual lifestyle changes with collective and systemic action. The most effective individual actions supported by scientific evidence include limiting family size, reducing car and air travel, adopting plant-based diets, and improving home energy efficiency. While some actions may be challenging due to personal, cultural, or economic reasons, even incremental changes contribute to broader environmental benefits. Importantly, individual efforts should be complemented by political advocacy to drive structural changes necessary for sustainable development.

